PN,41801
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1772010305
OL,3,CMeet Hugo, the first baby born in the
OL,4,CUK after womb transplant from dead
OL,5,Cdonor
OL,7,FA baby boy has become the first child
OL,8,Fin the UK to be born to a mother who
OL,9,Freceived a womb from a dead donor.
OL,11,FHugo Powell was delivered weighing 6lb
OL,12,F13oz (3.1kg) in December at Queen
OL,13,FCharlotte's and Chelsea Hospital, part
OL,14,Fof Imperial College Healthcare NHS
OL,15,FTrust.
OL,17,FThe transplant marks the first birth
OL,18,Fin the UK using a womb from a deceased
OL,19,Fdonor, with only two previous cases
OL,20,Fever reported in Europe.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/24
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1772010305
OL,3,CMeet Hugo, the first baby born in the
OL,4,CUK after womb transplant from dead
OL,5,Cdonor
OL,7,FLast year surgeons announced the UK's
OL,8,Ffirst baby born from a womb transplant
OL,9,Finvolving a living donor.
OL,11,FIn the latest case, Hugo's mother,
OL,12,FGrace Bell, an IT programme manager,
OL,13,Fwas born with Mayer-Rokitansky-Kuster-
OL,14,FHauser (MRKH), a rare condition
OL,15,Fresulting in an underdeveloped or
OL,16,Fmissing womb.
OL,18,FHis father, Steve Powell, works in
OL,19,Ffinance, and the couple, who are both
OL,20,Fin their 30s, live in the south of
OL,21,FEngland.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/24
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1772010305
OL,3,CMeet Hugo, the first baby born in the
OL,4,CUK after womb transplant from dead
OL,5,Cdonor
OL,7,FMs Bell, who was diagnosed with MRKH
OL,8,Fwhen she was 16, said: "It's simply a
OL,9,Fmiracle. I never, ever thought that
OL,10,Fthis would be possible.
OL,12,F"I'm the happiest I've ever been in my
OL,13,Flife."
OL,15,FDescribing Hugo's birth by Caesarean
OL,16,Fsection, she said: "I remember there
OL,17,Fwas lots and lots of people in the
OL,18,Froom running around.
OL,20,F"I was holding Steve's hand at the
OL,21,Ftime...
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/24
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1772010305
OL,3,CMeet Hugo, the first baby born in the
OL,4,CUK after womb transplant from dead
OL,5,Cdonor
OL,7,F"I remember trying to peek over the
OL,8,Fdrapes, and Hugo finally got put in my
OL,9,Farms, and this being the moment that
OL,10,Feveryone has been working so hard to
OL,11,Fachieve.
OL,13,F"Since I was 16, I never thought this
OL,14,Fwas going to be possible. So it really
OL,15,Fis a miracle.
OL,17,F"It just felt quite unreal at the time
OL,18,Fbecause this has been a long journey
OL,19,Ffor us both.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/24
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1772010305
OL,3,CMeet Hugo, the first baby born in the
OL,4,CUK after womb transplant from dead
OL,5,Cdonor
OL,7,F"I remember waking up in the morning
OL,8,Fand seeing his little face, with his
OL,9,Flittle dummy in, and it felt like I
OL,10,Fneeded to wake up from a dream.
OL,12,F"It was just incredible."
OL,14,FMr Powell said: "When he came over the
OL,15,Fcurtain, it was just sort of
OL,16,Foverwhelming emotions. I felt like I
OL,17,Fwanted to cry but couldn't.
OL,26,@vD@QOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/24
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1772010305
OL,3,CMeet Hugo, the first baby born in the
OL,4,CUK after womb transplant from dead
OL,5,Cdonor
OL,7,F"From where we started ` first meeting
OL,8,F` to where we are today, with Hugo, is
OL,9,Fnothing short of a miracle after
OL,10,Feverything we've been through."
OL,12,FMs Bell said she thinks of her womb
OL,13,Fdonor every day and the generosity of
OL,14,Fthe donor's family.
OL,16,F"There are no words to say thank you
OL,17,Fenough to my donor and her family,"
OL,18,Fshe said.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/24
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1772010305
OL,3,CMeet Hugo, the first baby born in the
OL,4,CUK after womb transplant from dead
OL,5,Cdonor
OL,7,F"Their kindness and selflessness to a
OL,8,Fcomplete stranger is the reason I have
OL,9,Fbeen able to fulfil my lifelong dream
OL,10,Fof being a mum.
OL,12,F"I hope they know that my child will
OL,13,Falways know of their incredible gift,
OL,14,Fand the miracle that brought him into
OL,15,Fthis world.
OL,17,F"I think of my donor and her family
OL,18,Fevery day and pray they find some
OL,19,Fpeace in knowing their daughter gave
OL,20,Fme the biggest gift, the gift of life.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/24
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41808
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1772010305
OL,3,CMeet Hugo, the first baby born in the
OL,4,CUK after womb transplant from dead
OL,5,Cdonor
OL,7,F"A part of her will live on forever."
OL,9,FBreaking down in tears, Ms Bell said
OL,10,Fthe couple were "in disbelief" when
OL,11,Fthey discovered she was pregnant,
OL,12,Fadding: "I felt the luckiest girl in
OL,13,Fthe world."
OL,15,FShe added: "This isn't a life-saving
OL,16,Fdonation but it is a life-giving one.
OL,18,F"From the moment of my diagnosis,
OL,19,Fevery birthday when I blew out my
OL,20,Fcandles, I would wish for this ` to be
OL,21,Fable to experience pregnancy.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/24
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41809
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1772010305
OL,3,CMeet Hugo, the first baby born in the
OL,4,CUK after womb transplant from dead
OL,5,Cdonor
OL,7,F"I want the donor's family to know how
OL,8,Fmuch of a gift they have given to me.
OL,10,F"They have fulfilled all of my dreams,
OL,11,Feverything has come true."
OL,13,FFive other organs from the donor were
OL,14,Ftransplanted into four people, saving
OL,15,Fthe lives of others.
OL,17,FHer parents said: "Losing our daughter
OL,18,Fhas shattered our world in ways we can
OL,19,Fbarely put into words.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G9/24
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41810
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1772010305
OL,3,CMeet Hugo, the first baby born in the
OL,4,CUK after womb transplant from dead
OL,5,Cdonor
OL,7,F"The grief is overwhelming and the
OL,8,Fache of her absence is something we
OL,9,Fwill carry forever.
OL,11,F"Yet even in this unimaginable pain,
OL,12,Fwe've found a small measure of solace
OL,13,Fin knowing that her final act, her
OL,14,Fchoice, was one of pure generosity.
OL,16,F"Through organ donation, she has given
OL,17,Fother families the precious gift of
OL,18,Ftime, hope, healing and now life.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G10/24
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41811
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1772010305
OL,3,CMeet Hugo, the first baby born in the
OL,4,CUK after womb transplant from dead
OL,5,Cdonor
OL,7,F"As her parents, we feel tremendous
OL,8,Fpride at the legacy she leaves behind
OL,9,F` a legacy of compassion, courage and
OL,10,Flove that continues to touch lives
OL,11,Feven after her passing.
OL,13,F"We urge others to consider donation
OL,14,Fso that more people in desperate need
OL,15,Fmay be given the chance to live, just
OL,16,Fas our daughter so selflessly wished."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G11/24
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41812
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1772010305
OL,3,CMeet Hugo, the first baby born in the
OL,4,CUK after womb transplant from dead
OL,5,Cdonor
OL,7,FDescribing how she felt when told as a
OL,8,Fteenager that she had no womb, Ms Bell
OL,9,Fsaid she remembers "going into the
OL,10,Fhospital toilets and uncontrollably
OL,11,Fcrying".
OL,13,FOn meeting Mr Powell, she told him
OL,14,F"straight away" of her diagnosis, she
OL,15,Fsaid.
OL,17,FThe couple had chosen a surrogacy
OL,18,Froute in order to have a family but
OL,19,Fthen became involved in the womb
OL,20,Ftransplant programme.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G12/24
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41813
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1772010305
OL,3,CMeet Hugo, the first baby born in the
OL,4,CUK after womb transplant from dead
OL,5,Cdonor
OL,7,FThey decided to give Hugo the middle
OL,8,Fname Richard, after Professor Richard
OL,9,FSmith, clinical lead of the charity
OL,10,FWomb Transplant UK and consultant
OL,11,Fgynaecological surgeon at Imperial
OL,12,FCollege Healthcare NHS Trust.
OL,14,FHugo was also given the name Norman in
OL,15,Fhonour of Ms Bell's grandfather, so
OL,16,Fhis full name is Hugo Richard Norman
OL,17,FPowell.
OL,19,FProf Smith, who was present at the
OL,20,Fbirth said: "It's been an unbelievable
OL,21,Fjourney.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G13/24
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41814
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1772010305
OL,3,CMeet Hugo, the first baby born in the
OL,4,CUK after womb transplant from dead
OL,5,Cdonor
OL,7,F"Our whole team has been hanging
OL,8,Ftogether now for years and years to
OL,9,Fmake this happen.
OL,11,F"So to me, it's been fantastic, just
OL,12,Famazing."
OL,14,FOn holding baby Hugo and hearing he
OL,15,Fwould be given his name, Prof Smith
OL,16,Fsaid: "This brought a tear to my eye.
OL,18,F"As the baby was handed over, the
OL,19,Fparents said they were actually going
OL,20,Fto call the baby Hugo Richard.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G14/24
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41815
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1772010305
OL,3,CMeet Hugo, the first baby born in the
OL,4,CUK after womb transplant from dead
OL,5,Cdonor
OL,7,F"I've delivered over 1,000 babies in
OL,8,Fmy life. Never has a baby been named
OL,9,Fafter me.
OL,11,F"That did make me cry, straight up.
OL,12,FIt's been quite emotional, very
OL,13,Femotional."
OL,15,FProf Smith said the atmosphere in the
OL,16,Froom was "absolutely filled with joy".
OL,18,FHe said: "There was massive joy when
OL,19,Fthe baby was born, this new life in
OL,20,Fthe world. It was fantastic."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G15/24
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41816
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1772010305
OL,3,CMeet Hugo, the first baby born in the
OL,4,CUK after womb transplant from dead
OL,5,Cdonor
OL,7,FAbout 25 to 30 babies have been born
OL,8,Fworldwide from deceased womb donation.
OL,10,FMore than two thirds of womb
OL,11,Ftransplants generally involve living
OL,12,Fdonors, while a third come from
OL,13,Fdeceased donors.
OL,15,FIsabel Quiroga, consultant surgeon and
OL,16,Fclinical lead for organ retrieval at
OL,17,Fthe Oxford Transplant Centre, part of
OL,18,FOxford University Hospitals, carried
OL,19,Fout the seven-hour womb transplant on
OL,20,FMs Bell there in 2024.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G16/24
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41817
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1772010305
OL,3,CMeet Hugo, the first baby born in the
OL,4,CUK after womb transplant from dead
OL,5,Cdonor
OL,7,FSeveral months later, Ms Bell
OL,8,Funderwent fertility treatment at The
OL,9,FLister Fertility Clinic in London.
OL,11,FMiss Quiroga said: "It has been a long
OL,12,Fjourney, and certainly we are
OL,13,Fdelighted, especially for our patient,
OL,14,Fwho's been in our programme for a good
OL,15,Fnumber of years.
OL,17,F"Her dream has been to be a mother, so
OL,18,Fwe are totally elated."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G17/24
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41818
SC,0018
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1772010305
OL,3,CMeet Hugo, the first baby born in the
OL,4,CUK after womb transplant from dead
OL,5,Cdonor
OL,7,FMiss Quiroga said the donor family's
OL,8,Fdecision to donate their daughter's
OL,9,Forgans "saved multiple lives".
OL,11,FShe added: "In deciding to also then
OL,12,Fdonate her womb, they have also helped
OL,13,Fto create a new life. This is
OL,14,Fextraordinary and we now have a
OL,15,Fhealthy baby boy."
OL,17,FMs Bell and Mr Powell may decide to
OL,18,Fhave a second baby, after which
OL,19,Fsurgeons will remove the transplanted
OL,20,Fwomb.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G18/24
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41819
SC,0019
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1772010305
OL,3,CMeet Hugo, the first baby born in the
OL,4,CUK after womb transplant from dead
OL,5,Cdonor
OL,7,FIf it was left in situ, Ms Bell would
OL,8,Fface a lifetime of immunosuppressant
OL,9,Fdrugs, which carry risks.
OL,11,FWomb Transplant UK has now performed
OL,12,Fand paid for five womb transplants in
OL,13,Fthe UK so far ` two involving a living
OL,14,Fdonor and three using a deceased donor.
OL,16,FTwo babies have been born and three
OL,17,Ftransplant patients have not had a
OL,18,Fbaby yet, but are undergoing private
OL,19,FIVF.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G19/24
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41820
SC,0020
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1772010305
OL,3,CMeet Hugo, the first baby born in the
OL,4,CUK after womb transplant from dead
OL,5,Cdonor
OL,7,F"They have functioning transplants,"
OL,8,FMiss Quiroga said. "So far, we haven't
OL,9,Fhad any technical failures ` and they
OL,10,Fare at different stages with IVF and
OL,11,Fembryo transfer."
OL,13,FHugo's birth follows the UK's first
OL,14,Fwomb transplant in 2023, which
OL,15,Finvolved Grace Davidson, another MRKH
OL,16,Fpatient, receiving a womb ` also
OL,17,Fcalled the uterus ` from her older
OL,18,Fsister, Amy, in a living donation.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G20/24
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
