OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41822
SC,0022
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1772010305
OL,3,CMeet Hugo, the first baby born in the
OL,4,CUK after womb transplant from dead
OL,5,Cdonor
OL,7,FBecky Clarke, regional head of nursing
OL,8,Ffor the Midlands and South Central
OL,9,FOrgan Donation Teams at NHS Blood and
OL,10,FTransplant, said: "Our specialist
OL,11,Fnurses for organ donation are highly
OL,12,Ftrained, experienced nurses who will
OL,13,Fspeak to families at the time their
OL,14,Floved one has sadly died, and approach
OL,15,Fthem around organ donation.
OL,17,F"They will check whether the person's
OL,18,Fon the Organ Donor Register, and then
OL,19,Fspeak with the family and see whether
OL,20,Fit's something they're in agreement
OL,21,Fwith.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G22/24
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41823
SC,0023
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1772010305
OL,3,CMeet Hugo, the first baby born in the
OL,4,CUK after womb transplant from dead
OL,5,Cdonor
OL,7,F"Once we've ascertained that, then we
OL,8,Fwould seek further consent from the
OL,9,Ffamilies and approach them if they
OL,10,Fwant to consider, as an extra consent,
OL,11,Fto womb donation.
OL,13,F"Our experience of approaching the
OL,14,Fsmall number of families is the vast
OL,15,Fmajority have immediately wanted to
OL,16,Fagree.
OL,18,F"They think it's a wonderful thing to
OL,19,Fdo.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G23/24
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
